https://youtu.be/7f2wg1pqQDs?t=29

Faggots would be shocked if they knew how much our economic system is dependent on robots already, but they're not the kind of shit you'll hear about on the news. Just dumb machines designed to carry out boring tasks repeatedly with better and better sensory abilities every iteration in technology and economic feasibility.

Making humanoid robots - in the old days especially - was always limited by power, speed, and onboard capacity. It's a lot better now, but people like Musk are still selling essentially the same old 'two more weeks' bullshit as they were decades ago. We'll no doubt get there eventually, but notice your Roomba doesn't look like Rosie from the Jetsons, and is still probably still getting stuck on the edge of your rug, or sucking up the cat's tail occasionally, just less and less often with every new model.

I'm actually very interested in disability tech and the economics are a real bitch. Hopefully 3D printing and some kind of modular tech will improve that situation over time. There sure are a lot of unnecessary complications with the medical and insurance industry, and it should be simpler than it is right now.

The real Holy Grail for actuators would be where you could just just duplicate the skeleton and musculature on a one-to-one scale and weight, but the biological interface and feedback are the real bitch.

>>179190470
Tolkien wasn't afraid to portray them as genuinely superior, but distant and waning. They're beautiful, kind, intelligent, and gracious, but in the back of your mind, and theirs, you know that they're doomed to fade from this world, and either remain as shadows of what they once were, or leave it forever to somewhere you cannot follow. And this sadness permeates every part of them. It's why RoP failed before they'd even finished writing the script. You cannot write Tolkien's elves as the protagonists without pulling the camera back and portraying them as mythical figures. The idea of his elves being foolish, or clumsy, or ignorant, is repulsive to Tolkien fans at a primal level.

It's not really noticeable to the average viewer but next time you watch an actual episode of the show, take note of the soundtrack, and then if possible, rewatch everything on mute with subtitles. The producers always pipe through some sort of generic acoustic guitar muzak to accompany each scene in order to attempt to manipulate the viewer's emotions into feeling a certain way toward whatever Jazz is going through, whether it's a date or a botched surgery, or some staged family activity.

I don't know much about guitar but I do know several guitar players, and anyone who plays guitar knows that there are certain chords you can play to convey a happy, hopeful tone, and chords you can play to exhibit a sad, depressing tone. As far as I know, there's no real way to isolate the shitty stock audio soundtrack from the episode, but next time you're watching an episode, try to imagine the show without any music and just try to tune it out.

When we post soundless .webms, we get the raw fucked-up dialogue without any background music or emotional manipulation from that soundtrack. If they didn't have the music and just let the conversations and cuts play out as is, it would be truly horrifying, sort of like watching a bad sitcom without a laugh track to tell you how to feel almost feels sort of eerie.

Goku on the other hand is unchanging. He gets more powerful but his attitude is the same.

>>man I’m so cold, let me take off 1 shoe, walk a few miles, shred some more clothes, then dump my backpack down the mountain, then die

https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hypothermia#Paradoxical_undressing

"Twenty to fifty percent of hypothermia deaths are associated with paradoxical undressing. This typically occurs during moderate and severe hypothermia, as the person becomes disoriented, confused, and combative. They may begin discarding their clothing, which, in turn, increases the rate of heat loss.[21][22]

Rescuers who are trained in mountain survival techniques are taught to expect this; however, people who die from hypothermia in urban environments who are found in an undressed state are sometimes incorrectly assumed to have been subjected to sexual assault.[23]

One explanation for the effect is a cold-induced malfunction of the hypothalamus, the part of the brain that regulates body temperature. Another explanation is that the muscles contracting peripheral blood vessels become exhausted (known as a loss of vasomotor tone) and relax, leading to a sudden surge of blood (and heat) to the extremities, causing the person to feel overheated.[23][24]"

I'm a trans individual who has been on /tv/ for years. I've yet to see any definitive proof that anything which is largely accepted by the trans community is bad for them, and I'm here to address these issues.

Let's get a hot topic out of the way first: gender reassignment surgery is as necessary for individuals experiencing severe gender dysphoria as chemo would be for a cancer patient. Yes, some people still unfortunately kill themselves. But, every single person who undergoes surgery who doesnt is a person whose life is saved. It is not cosmetic, it is life saving.

Secondly, estrogen is not bad for your mind or body in any way as an assigned-at-birth male. There is zero scientific evidence that it is. This is baseless and only serves to scare people away from taking the medicine they need

Third: it can be "too late to change". I am 37 and I only began hrt 5 years ago. Within two years I was visually passing and now my voice sounds indistinguishable from any other woman's.

Finally, that it is bad for children to transition. Most children have no issue with this and think it's cool to know a trans individual. And giving children estrogen does in fact make it easier on them psychologically to go through their lives as a woman. There is zero evidence that any child has experienced adverse effects growing up compared to non-trans children.

I will talk to anyone about any of these things. I'm just sick of seeing baseless bullshit spewed about us on this board. Seeing that stuff early on in my transition made me think about some things I never want to think about again. And anyone who posts pictures of girls who are having trouble passing is participating in psychological abuse.
